snippet.textDisplay:
Who did the wheel alignments on these cars? Did you check the bushes and linkages, steering racks, blah blah etc?


When braking, wheel alignment and arm/bush/mechanical integrity are MASSIVELY important - smash the brake pedal, all the wheels toe-in or out, camber goes negative or positive, this hugely affects the tyre's ability to retard the vehicle, as you can have all 4 tyres fighting each other, pointing in different directions, but more importantly, pointing in a different direction that the car is heading in, reducing the frictional force of the ground vs tyre vs vehicle trajectory.


You can't really have an acceptable comparison without ensuring both vehicles are in excellent condition, "GOOD CONDITION" simply isn't good enough for a test, that I feel, is as important as this one, or these series of tests.
